President Donald J. Trump has announced several White House appointments. Captain Keith B. Davids has been appointed as Special Assistant to the President and Deputy Director of the White House Military Office. Zachary D. Fuentes will serve as Special Assistant to the President and Assistant to the Chief of Staff. Kirstjen M. Nielsen has been appointed as Assistant to the President and Principal Deputy Chief of Staff. Robert L. “Bobby” Peede will serve as Deputy Assistant to the President and Director of Presidential Advance. Lastly, Daniel P. Walsh has been appointed as Deputy Assistant to the President and Director of the White House Military Office.